The paper discusses the design and development of a data-driven machine learning-based application maintenance solution, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of theme mining and incident mapping, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY), respectively. The use of machine learning algorithms for incident ticket identification and assignee recommendation falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper emphasizes the need for designing pragmatic solutions with low barriers to adoption, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
